107# A global tracker to ensure that _setup() is called for every class, even 

108# if is has been called for a parent class. This allows different _fields 

109# definitions for child classes. Without such a construct, the child classes 

110# would just see the parent class attributes and would use them.

114def load(encoded_data, strict=False): 

115 """ 

116 Loads a BER/DER-encoded byte string and construct a universal object based 

117 on the tag value: 

118 

119 - 1: Boolean 

120 - 2: Integer 

121 - 3: BitString 

122 - 4: OctetString 

123 - 5: Null 

124 - 6: ObjectIdentifier 

125 - 7: ObjectDescriptor 

126 - 8: InstanceOf 

127 - 9: Real 

128 - 10: Enumerated 

129 - 11: EmbeddedPdv 

130 - 12: UTF8String 

131 - 13: RelativeOid 

132 - 16: Sequence, 

133 - 17: Set 

134 - 18: NumericString 

135 - 19: PrintableString 

136 - 20: TeletexString 

137 - 21: VideotexString 

138 - 22: IA5String 

139 - 23: UTCTime 

140 - 24: GeneralizedTime 

141 - 25: GraphicString 

142 - 26: VisibleString 

143 - 27: GeneralString 

144 - 28: UniversalString 

145 - 29: CharacterString 

146 - 30: BMPString 

147 

148 :param encoded_data: 

149 A byte string of BER or DER-encoded data 

150 

151 :param strict: 

152 A boolean indicating if trailing data should be forbidden - if so, a 

153 ValueError will be raised when trailing data exists 

154 

155 :raises: 

156 ValueError - when strict is True and trailing data is present 

157 ValueError - when the encoded value tag a tag other than listed above 

158 ValueError - when the ASN.1 header length is longer than the data 

159 TypeError - when encoded_data is not a byte string 

160 

161 :return: 

162 An instance of the one of the universal classes 

163 """ 

164 

165 return Asn1Value.load(encoded_data, strict=strict)

168class Asn1Value(object): 

169 """ 

170 The basis of all ASN.1 values 

171 """ 

172 

173 # The integer 0 for primitive, 1 for constructed 

174 method = None 

175 

176 # An integer 0 through 3 - see CLASS_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP for value 

177 class_ = None 

178 

179 # An integer 1 or greater indicating the tag number 

180 tag = None 

181 

182 # An alternate tag allowed for this type - used for handling broken 

183 # structures where a string value is encoded using an incorrect tag 

184 _bad_tag = None 

185 

186 # If the value has been implicitly tagged 

187 implicit = False 

188 

189 # If explicitly tagged, a tuple of 2-element tuples containing the 

190 # class int and tag int, from innermost to outermost 

191 explicit = None 

192 

193 # The BER/DER header bytes 

194 _header = None 

195 

196 # Raw encoded value bytes not including class, method, tag, length header 

197 contents = None 

198 

199 # The BER/DER trailer bytes 

200 _trailer = b'' 

201 

202 # The native python representation of the value - this is not used by 

203 # some classes since they utilize _bytes or _unicode 

204 _native = None

206 @classmethod 

207 def load(cls, encoded_data, strict=False, **kwargs): 

208 """ 

209 Loads a BER/DER-encoded byte string using the current class as the spec 

210 

211 :param encoded_data: 

212 A byte string of BER or DER-encoded data 

213 

214 :param strict: 

215 A boolean indicating if trailing data should be forbidden - if so, a 

216 ValueError will be raised when trailing data exists 

217 

218 :return: 

219 An instance of the current class 

220 """ 

221 

222 if not isinstance(encoded_data, byte_cls): 

223 raise TypeError('encoded_data must be a byte string, not %s' % type_name(encoded_data)) 

224 

225 spec = None 

226 if cls.tag is not None: 

227 spec = cls 

228 

229 value, _ = _parse_build(encoded_data, spec=spec, spec_params=kwargs, strict=strict) 

230 return value

232 def __init__(self, explicit=None, implicit=None, no_explicit=False, tag_type=None, class_=None, tag=None, 

233 optional=None, default=None, contents=None): 

234 """ 

235 The optional parameter is not used, but rather included so we don't 

236 have to delete it from the parameter dictionary when passing as keyword 

237 args 

238 

239 :param explicit: 

240 An int tag number for explicit tagging, or a 2-element tuple of 

241 class and tag. 

242 

243 :param implicit: 

244 An int tag number for implicit tagging, or a 2-element tuple of 

245 class and tag. 

246 

247 :param no_explicit: 

248 If explicit tagging info should be removed from this instance. 

249 Used internally to allow contructing the underlying value that 

250 has been wrapped in an explicit tag. 

251 

252 :param tag_type: 

253 None for normal values, or one of "implicit", "explicit" for tagged 

254 values. Deprecated in favor of explicit and implicit params. 

255 

256 :param class_: 

257 The class for the value - defaults to "universal" if tag_type is 

258 None, otherwise defaults to "context". Valid values include: 

259 - "universal" 

260 - "application" 

261 - "context" 

262 - "private" 

263 Deprecated in favor of explicit and implicit params. 

264 

265 :param tag: 

266 The integer tag to override - usually this is used with tag_type or 

267 class_. Deprecated in favor of explicit and implicit params. 

268 

269 :param optional: 

270 Dummy parameter that allows "optional" key in spec param dicts 

271 

272 :param default: 

273 The default value to use if the value is currently None 

274 

275 :param contents: 

276 A byte string of the encoded contents of the value 

277 

278 :raises: 

279 ValueError - when implicit, explicit, tag_type, class_ or tag are invalid values 

280 """ 

281 

282 try: 

283 if self.__class__ not in _SETUP_CLASSES: 

284 cls = self.__class__ 

285 # Allow explicit to be specified as a simple 2-element tuple 

286 # instead of requiring the user make a nested tuple 

287 if cls.explicit is not None and isinstance(cls.explicit[0], int_types): 

288 cls.explicit = (cls.explicit, ) 

289 if hasattr(cls, '_setup'): 

290 self._setup() 

291 _SETUP_CLASSES[cls] = True 

292 

293 # Normalize tagging values 

294 if explicit is not None: 

295 if isinstance(explicit, int_types): 

296 if class_ is None: 

297 class_ = 'context' 

298 explicit = (class_, explicit) 

299 # Prevent both explicit and tag_type == 'explicit' 

300 if tag_type == 'explicit': 

301 tag_type = None 

302 tag = None 

303 

304 if implicit is not None: 

305 if isinstance(implicit, int_types): 

306 if class_ is None: 

307 class_ = 'context' 

308 implicit = (class_, implicit) 

309 # Prevent both implicit and tag_type == 'implicit' 

310 if tag_type == 'implicit': 

311 tag_type = None 

312 tag = None 

313 

314 # Convert old tag_type API to explicit/implicit params 

315 if tag_type is not None: 

316 if class_ is None: 

317 class_ = 'context' 

318 if tag_type == 'explicit': 

319 explicit = (class_, tag) 

320 elif tag_type == 'implicit': 

321 implicit = (class_, tag) 

322 else: 

323 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

324 ''' 

325 tag_type must be one of "implicit", "explicit", not %s 

326 ''', 

327 repr(tag_type) 

328 )) 

329 

330 if explicit is not None: 

331 # Ensure we have a tuple of 2-element tuples 

332 if len(explicit) == 2 and isinstance(explicit[1], int_types): 

333 explicit = (explicit, ) 

334 for class_, tag in explicit: 

335 invalid_class = None 

336 if isinstance(class_, int_types): 

337 if class_ not in CLASS_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP: 

338 invalid_class = class_ 

339 else: 

340 if class_ not in CLASS_NAME_TO_NUM_MAP: 

341 invalid_class = class_ 

342 class_ = CLASS_NAME_TO_NUM_MAP[class_] 

343 if invalid_class is not None: 

344 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

345 ''' 

346 explicit class must be one of "universal", "application", 

347 "context", "private", not %s 

348 ''', 

349 repr(invalid_class) 

350 )) 

351 if tag is not None: 

352 if not isinstance(tag, int_types): 

353 raise TypeError(unwrap( 

354 ''' 

355 explicit tag must be an integer, not %s 

356 ''', 

357 type_name(tag) 

358 )) 

359 if self.explicit is None: 

360 self.explicit = ((class_, tag), ) 

361 else: 

362 self.explicit = self.explicit + ((class_, tag), ) 

363 

364 elif implicit is not None: 

365 class_, tag = implicit 

366 if class_ not in CLASS_NAME_TO_NUM_MAP: 

367 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

368 ''' 

369 implicit class must be one of "universal", "application", 

370 "context", "private", not %s 

371 ''', 

372 repr(class_) 

373 )) 

374 if tag is not None: 

375 if not isinstance(tag, int_types): 

376 raise TypeError(unwrap( 

377 ''' 

378 implicit tag must be an integer, not %s 

379 ''', 

380 type_name(tag) 

381 )) 

382 self.class_ = CLASS_NAME_TO_NUM_MAP[class_] 

383 self.tag = tag 

384 self.implicit = True 

385 else: 

386 if class_ is not None: 

387 if class_ not in CLASS_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP: 

388 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

389 ''' 

390 class_ must be one of "universal", "application", 

391 "context", "private", not %s 

392 ''', 

393 repr(class_) 

394 )) 

395 self.class_ = CLASS_NAME_TO_NUM_MAP[class_] 

396 

397 if tag is not None: 

398 self.tag = tag 

399 

400 if no_explicit: 

401 self.explicit = None 

402 

403 if contents is not None: 

404 self.contents = contents 

405 

406 elif default is not None: 

407 self.set(default) 

408 

409 except (ValueError, TypeError) as e: 

410 args = e.args[1:] 

411 e.args = (e.args[0] + '\n while constructing %s' % type_name(self),) + args 

412 raise e

414 def __str__(self): 

415 """ 

416 Since str is different in Python 2 and 3, this calls the appropriate 

417 method, __unicode__() or __bytes__() 

418 

419 :return: 

420 A unicode string 

421 """ 

422 

423 if _PY2: 

424 return self.__bytes__() 

425 else: 

426 return self.__unicode__()

428 def __repr__(self): 

429 """ 

430 :return: 

431 A unicode string 

432 """ 

433 

434 if _PY2: 

435 return '<%s %s b%s>' % (type_name(self), id(self), repr(self.dump())) 

436 else: 

437 return '<%s %s %s>' % (type_name(self), id(self), repr(self.dump()))

459 def _new_instance(self): 

460 """ 

461 Constructs a new copy of the current object, preserving any tagging

463 :return: 

464 An Asn1Value object 

465 """ 

466 

467 new_obj = self.__class__() 

468 new_obj.class_ = self.class_

512 def retag(self, tagging, tag=None): 

513 """ 

514 Copies the object, applying a new tagging to it 

515 

516 :param tagging: 

517 A dict containing the keys "explicit" and "implicit". Legacy 

518 API allows a unicode string of "implicit" or "explicit". 

519 

520 :param tag: 

521 A integer tag number. Only used when tagging is a unicode string. 

522 

523 :return: 

524 An Asn1Value object 

525 """ 

526 

527 # This is required to preserve the old API 

528 if not isinstance(tagging, dict): 

529 tagging = {tagging: tag} 

530 new_obj = self.__class__(explicit=tagging.get('explicit'), implicit=tagging.get('implicit')) 

531 new_obj._copy(self, copy.deepcopy) 

532 return new_obj

546 def _copy(self, other, copy_func): 

547 """ 

548 Copies the contents of another Asn1Value object to itself 

549 

550 :param object: 

551 Another instance of the same class 

552 

553 :param copy_func: 

554 An reference of copy.copy() or copy.deepcopy() to use when copying 

555 lists, dicts and objects 

556 """ 

557 

558 if self.__class__ != other.__class__: 

559 raise TypeError(unwrap( 

560 ''' 

561 Can not copy values from %s object to %s object 

562 ''', 

563 type_name(other), 

564 type_name(self) 

565 )) 

566 

567 self.contents = other.contents 

568 self._native = copy_func(other._native)

570 def debug(self, nest_level=1): 

571 """ 

572 Show the binary data and parsed data in a tree structure 

573 """ 

574 

575 prefix = ' ' * nest_level 

576 

577 # This interacts with Any and moves the tag, implicit, explicit, _header, 

578 # contents, _footer to the parsed value so duplicate data isn't present 

579 has_parsed = hasattr(self, 'parsed') 

580 

581 _basic_debug(prefix, self) 

582 if has_parsed: 

583 self.parsed.debug(nest_level + 2) 

584 elif hasattr(self, 'chosen'): 

585 self.chosen.debug(nest_level + 2) 

586 else: 

587 if _PY2 and isinstance(self.native, byte_cls): 

588 print('%s Native: b%s' % (prefix, repr(self.native))) 

589 else: 

590 print('%s Native: %s' % (prefix, self.native))

592 def dump(self, force=False): 

593 """ 

594 Encodes the value using DER 

595 

596 :param force: 

597 If the encoded contents already exist, clear them and regenerate 

598 to ensure they are in DER format instead of BER format 

599 

600 :return: 

601 A byte string of the DER-encoded value 

602 """ 

603 

604 contents = self.contents 

605 

606 if self._header is None or force: 

607 if isinstance(self, Constructable) and self._indefinite: 

608 self.method = 0 

609 

610 header = _dump_header(self.class_, self.method, self.tag, self.contents) 

611 

612 if self.explicit is not None: 

613 for class_, tag in self.explicit: 

614 header = _dump_header(class_, 1, tag, header + self.contents) + header 

615 

616 self._header = header 

617 self._trailer = b'' 

618 

619 return self._header + contents

622class ValueMap(): 

623 """ 

624 Basic functionality that allows for mapping values from ints or OIDs to 

625 python unicode strings 

626 """ 

627 

628 # A dict from primitive value (int or OID) to unicode string. This needs 

629 # to be defined in the source code 

630 _map = None 

631 

632 # A dict from unicode string to int/OID. This is automatically generated 

633 # from _map the first time it is needed 

634 _reverse_map = None 

635 

636 def _setup(self): 

637 """ 

638 Generates _reverse_map from _map 

639 """ 

640 

641 cls = self.__class__ 

642 if cls._map is None or cls._reverse_map is not None: 

643 return 

644 cls._reverse_map = {} 

645 for key, value in cls._map.items(): 

646 cls._reverse_map[value] = key

649class Castable(object): 

650 """ 

651 A mixin to handle converting an object between different classes that 

652 represent the same encoded value, but with different rules for converting 

653 to and from native Python values 

654 """ 

655 

656 def cast(self, other_class): 

657 """ 

658 Converts the current object into an object of a different class. The 

659 new class must use the ASN.1 encoding for the value. 

660 

661 :param other_class: 

662 The class to instantiate the new object from 

663 

664 :return: 

665 An instance of the type other_class 

666 """ 

667 

668 if other_class.tag != self.__class__.tag: 

669 raise TypeError(unwrap( 

670 ''' 

671 Can not covert a value from %s object to %s object since they 

672 use different tags: %d versus %d 

673 ''', 

674 type_name(other_class), 

675 type_name(self), 

676 other_class.tag, 

677 self.__class__.tag 

678 )) 

679 

680 new_obj = other_class() 

681 new_obj.class_ = self.class_ 

682 new_obj.implicit = self.implicit 

683 new_obj.explicit = self.explicit 

684 new_obj._header = self._header 

685 new_obj.contents = self.contents 

686 new_obj._trailer = self._trailer 

687 if isinstance(self, Constructable): 

688 new_obj.method = self.method 

689 new_obj._indefinite = self._indefinite 

690 return new_obj

693class Constructable(object): 

694 """ 

695 A mixin to handle string types that may be constructed from chunks 

696 contained within an indefinite length BER-encoded container 

697 """ 

698 

699 # Instance attribute indicating if an object was indefinite 

700 # length when parsed - affects parsing and dumping 

701 _indefinite = False 

702 

703 # Class attribute that indicates the offset into self.contents 

704 # that contains the chunks of data to merge 

705 _chunks_offset = 0 

706 

707 def _merge_chunks(self): 

708 """ 

709 :return: 

710 A concatenation of the native values of the contained chunks 

711 """ 

712 

713 if not self._indefinite: 

714 return self._as_chunk() 

715 

716 pointer = self._chunks_offset 

717 contents_len = len(self.contents) 

718 output = None 

719 

720 while pointer < contents_len: 

721 # We pass the current class as the spec so content semantics are preserved 

722 sub_value, pointer = _parse_build(self.contents, pointer, spec=self.__class__) 

723 if output is None: 

724 output = sub_value._merge_chunks() 

725 else: 

726 output += sub_value._merge_chunks() 

727 

728 if output is None: 

729 return self._as_chunk() 

730 

731 return output 

732 

733 def _as_chunk(self): 

734 """ 

735 A method to return a chunk of data that can be combined for 

736 constructed method values 

737 

738 :return: 

739 A native Python value that can be added together. Examples include 

740 byte strings, unicode strings or tuples. 

741 """ 

742 

743 if self._chunks_offset == 0: 

744 return self.contents 

745 return self.contents[self._chunks_offset:] 

746 

747 def _copy(self, other, copy_func): 

748 """ 

749 Copies the contents of another Constructable object to itself 

750 

751 :param object: 

752 Another instance of the same class 

753 

754 :param copy_func: 

755 An reference of copy.copy() or copy.deepcopy() to use when copying 

756 lists, dicts and objects 

757 """ 

758 

759 super(Constructable, self)._copy(other, copy_func) 

760 self.method = other.method 

761 self._indefinite = other._indefinite

821class Any(Asn1Value): 

822 """ 

823 A value class that can contain any value, and allows for easy parsing of 

824 the underlying encoded value using a spec. This is normally contained in 

825 a Structure that has an ObjectIdentifier field and _oid_pair and _oid_specs 

826 defined. 

827 """ 

828 

829 # The parsed value object 

830 _parsed = None 

831 

832 def __init__(self, value=None, **kwargs): 

833 """ 

834 Sets the value of the object before passing to Asn1Value.__init__() 

835 

836 :param value: 

837 An Asn1Value object that will be set as the parsed value 

838 """ 

839 

840 Asn1Value.__init__(self, **kwargs) 

841 

842 try: 

843 if value is not None: 

844 if not isinstance(value, Asn1Value): 

845 raise TypeError(unwrap( 

846 ''' 

847 value must be an instance of Asn1Value, not %s 

848 ''', 

849 type_name(value) 

850 )) 

851 

852 self._parsed = (value, value.__class__, None) 

853 self.contents = value.dump() 

854 

855 except (ValueError, TypeError) as e: 

856 args = e.args[1:] 

857 e.args = (e.args[0] + '\n while constructing %s' % type_name(self),) + args 

858 raise e 

859 

860 @property 

861 def native(self): 

862 """ 

863 The a native Python datatype representation of this value 

864 

865 :return: 

866 The .native value from the parsed value object 

867 """ 

868 

869 if self._parsed is None: 

870 self.parse() 

871 

872 return self._parsed[0].native 

873 

874 @property 

875 def parsed(self): 

876 """ 

877 Returns the parsed object from .parse() 

878 

879 :return: 

880 The object returned by .parse() 

881 """ 

882 

883 if self._parsed is None: 

884 self.parse() 

885 

886 return self._parsed[0] 

887 

888 def parse(self, spec=None, spec_params=None): 

889 """ 

890 Parses the contents generically, or using a spec with optional params 

891 

892 :param spec: 

893 A class derived from Asn1Value that defines what class_ and tag the 

894 value should have, and the semantics of the encoded value. The 

895 return value will be of this type. If omitted, the encoded value 

896 will be decoded using the standard universal tag based on the 

897 encoded tag number. 

898 

899 :param spec_params: 

900 A dict of params to pass to the spec object 

901 

902 :return: 

903 An object of the type spec, or if not present, a child of Asn1Value 

904 """ 

905 

906 if self._parsed is None or self._parsed[1:3] != (spec, spec_params): 

907 try: 

908 passed_params = spec_params or {} 

909 _tag_type_to_explicit_implicit(passed_params) 

910 if self.explicit is not None: 

911 if 'explicit' in passed_params: 

912 passed_params['explicit'] = self.explicit + passed_params['explicit'] 

913 else: 

914 passed_params['explicit'] = self.explicit 

915 contents = self._header + self.contents + self._trailer 

916 parsed_value, _ = _parse_build( 

917 contents, 

918 spec=spec, 

919 spec_params=passed_params 

920 ) 

921 self._parsed = (parsed_value, spec, spec_params) 

922 

923 # Once we've parsed the Any value, clear any attributes from this object 

924 # since they are now duplicate 

925 self.tag = None 

926 self.explicit = None 

927 self.implicit = False 

928 self._header = b'' 

929 self.contents = contents 

930 self._trailer = b'' 

931 

932 except (ValueError, TypeError) as e: 

933 args = e.args[1:] 

934 e.args = (e.args[0] + '\n while parsing %s' % type_name(self),) + args 

935 raise e 

936 return self._parsed[0]

938 def _copy(self, other, copy_func): 

939 """ 

940 Copies the contents of another Any object to itself 

941 

942 :param object: 

943 Another instance of the same class 

944 

945 :param copy_func: 

946 An reference of copy.copy() or copy.deepcopy() to use when copying 

947 lists, dicts and objects 

948 """ 

949 

950 super(Any, self)._copy(other, copy_func) 

951 self._parsed = copy_func(other._parsed)

953 def dump(self, force=False): 

954 """ 

955 Encodes the value using DER 

956 

957 :param force: 

958 If the encoded contents already exist, clear them and regenerate 

959 to ensure they are in DER format instead of BER format 

960 

961 :return: 

962 A byte string of the DER-encoded value 

963 """ 

964 

965 if self._parsed is None: 

966 self.parse() 

967 

968 return self._parsed[0].dump(force=force)

971class Choice(Asn1Value): 

972 """ 

973 A class to handle when a value may be one of several options 

974 """ 

975 

976 # The index in _alternatives of the validated alternative 

977 _choice = None 

978 

979 # The name of the chosen alternative 

980 _name = None 

981 

982 # The Asn1Value object for the chosen alternative 

983 _parsed = None 

984 

985 # A list of tuples in one of the following forms. 

986 # 

987 # Option 1, a unicode string field name and a value class 

988 # 

989 # ("name", Asn1ValueClass) 

990 # 

991 # Option 2, same as Option 1, but with a dict of class params 

992 # 

993 # ("name", Asn1ValueClass, {'explicit': 5}) 

994 _alternatives = None 

995 

996 # A dict that maps tuples of (class_, tag) to an index in _alternatives 

997 _id_map = None 

998 

999 # A dict that maps alternative names to an index in _alternatives 

1000 _name_map = None 

1001 

1002 @classmethod 

1003 def load(cls, encoded_data, strict=False, **kwargs): 

1004 """ 

1005 Loads a BER/DER-encoded byte string using the current class as the spec 

1006 

1007 :param encoded_data: 

1008 A byte string of BER or DER encoded data 

1009 

1010 :param strict: 

1011 A boolean indicating if trailing data should be forbidden - if so, a 

1012 ValueError will be raised when trailing data exists 

1013 

1014 :return: 

1015 A instance of the current class 

1016 """ 

1017 

1018 if not isinstance(encoded_data, byte_cls): 

1019 raise TypeError('encoded_data must be a byte string, not %s' % type_name(encoded_data)) 

1020 

1021 value, _ = _parse_build(encoded_data, spec=cls, spec_params=kwargs, strict=strict) 

1022 return value 

1023 

1024 def _setup(self): 

1025 """ 

1026 Generates _id_map from _alternatives to allow validating contents 

1027 """ 

1028 

1029 cls = self.__class__ 

1030 cls._id_map = {} 

1031 cls._name_map = {} 

1032 for index, info in enumerate(cls._alternatives): 

1033 if len(info) < 3: 

1034 info = info + ({},) 

1035 cls._alternatives[index] = info 

1036 id_ = _build_id_tuple(info[2], info[1]) 

1037 cls._id_map[id_] = index 

1038 cls._name_map[info[0]] = index 

1039 

1040 def __init__(self, name=None, value=None, **kwargs): 

1041 """ 

1042 Checks to ensure implicit tagging is not being used since it is 

1043 incompatible with Choice, then forwards on to Asn1Value.__init__() 

1044 

1045 :param name: 

1046 The name of the alternative to be set - used with value. 

1047 Alternatively this may be a dict with a single key being the name 

1048 and the value being the value, or a two-element tuple of the the 

1049 name and the value. 

1050 

1051 :param value: 

1052 The alternative value to set - used with name 

1053 

1054 :raises: 

1055 ValueError - when implicit param is passed (or legacy tag_type param is "implicit") 

1056 """ 

1057 

1058 _tag_type_to_explicit_implicit(kwargs) 

1059 

1060 Asn1Value.__init__(self, **kwargs) 

1061 

1062 try: 

1063 if kwargs.get('implicit') is not None: 

1064 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

1065 ''' 

1066 The Choice type can not be implicitly tagged even if in an 

1067 implicit module - due to its nature any tagging must be 

1068 explicit 

1069 ''' 

1070 )) 

1071 

1072 if name is not None: 

1073 if isinstance(name, dict): 

1074 if len(name) != 1: 

1075 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

1076 ''' 

1077 When passing a dict as the "name" argument to %s, 

1078 it must have a single key/value - however %d were 

1079 present 

1080 ''', 

1081 type_name(self), 

1082 len(name) 

1083 )) 

1084 name, value = list(name.items())[0] 

1085 

1086 if isinstance(name, tuple): 

1087 if len(name) != 2: 

1088 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

1089 ''' 

1090 When passing a tuple as the "name" argument to %s, 

1091 it must have two elements, the name and value - 

1092 however %d were present 

1093 ''', 

1094 type_name(self), 

1095 len(name) 

1096 )) 

1097 value = name[1] 

1098 name = name[0] 

1099 

1100 if name not in self._name_map: 

1101 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

1102 ''' 

1103 The name specified, "%s", is not a valid alternative 

1104 for %s 

1105 ''', 

1106 name, 

1107 type_name(self) 

1108 )) 

1109 

1110 self._choice = self._name_map[name] 

1111 _, spec, params = self._alternatives[self._choice] 

1112 

1113 if not isinstance(value, spec): 

1114 value = spec(value, **params) 

1115 else: 

1116 value = _fix_tagging(value, params) 

1117 self._parsed = value 

1118 

1119 except (ValueError, TypeError) as e: 

1120 args = e.args[1:] 

1121 e.args = (e.args[0] + '\n while constructing %s' % type_name(self),) + args 

1122 raise e 

1123 

1124 @property 

1125 def name(self): 

1126 """ 

1127 :return: 

1128 A unicode string of the field name of the chosen alternative 

1129 """ 

1130 if not self._name: 

1131 self._name = self._alternatives[self._choice][0] 

1132 return self._name

1134 def parse(self): 

1135 """ 

1136 Parses the detected alternative 

1137 

1138 :return: 

1139 An Asn1Value object of the chosen alternative 

1140 """ 

1141 

1142 if self._parsed is not None: 

1143 return self._parsed 

1144 

1145 try: 

1146 _, spec, params = self._alternatives[self._choice] 

1147 self._parsed, _ = _parse_build(self.contents, spec=spec, spec_params=params) 

1148 except (ValueError, TypeError) as e: 

1149 args = e.args[1:] 

1150 e.args = (e.args[0] + '\n while parsing %s' % type_name(self),) + args 

1151 raise e

1153 @property 

1154 def chosen(self): 

1155 """ 

1156 :return: 

1157 An Asn1Value object of the chosen alternative 

1158 """ 

1159 

1160 return self.parse()

1164 """ 

1165 The a native Python datatype representation of this value 

1166 

1167 :return: 

1168 The .native value from the contained value object 

1169 """ 

1170 

1171 return self.chosen.native

1173 def validate(self, class_, tag, contents): 

1174 """ 

1175 Ensures that the class and tag specified exist as an alternative 

1176 

1177 :param class_: 

1178 The integer class_ from the encoded value header 

1179 

1180 :param tag: 

1181 The integer tag from the encoded value header 

1182 

1183 :param contents: 

1184 A byte string of the contents of the value - used when the object 

1185 is explicitly tagged 

1186 

1187 :raises: 

1188 ValueError - when value is not a valid alternative 

1189 """ 

1190 

1191 id_ = (class_, tag) 

1192 

1193 if self.explicit is not None: 

1194 if self.explicit[-1] != id_: 

1195 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

1196 ''' 

1197 %s was explicitly tagged, but the value provided does not 

1198 match the class and tag 

1199 ''', 

1200 type_name(self) 

1201 )) 

1202 

1203 ((class_, _, tag, _, _, _), _) = _parse(contents, len(contents)) 

1204 id_ = (class_, tag) 

1205 

1206 if id_ in self._id_map: 

1207 self._choice = self._id_map[id_] 

1208 return 

1209 

1210 # This means the Choice was implicitly tagged 

1211 if self.class_ is not None and self.tag is not None: 

1212 if len(self._alternatives) > 1: 

1213 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

1214 ''' 

1215 %s was implicitly tagged, but more than one alternative 

1216 exists 

1217 ''', 

1218 type_name(self) 

1219 )) 

1220 if id_ == (self.class_, self.tag): 

1221 self._choice = 0 

1222 return 

1223 

1224 asn1 = self._format_class_tag(class_, tag) 

1225 asn1s = [self._format_class_tag(pair[0], pair[1]) for pair in self._id_map] 

1226 

1227 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

1228 ''' 

1229 Value %s did not match the class and tag of any of the alternatives 

1230 in %s: %s 

1231 ''', 

1232 asn1, 

1233 type_name(self), 

1234 ', '.join(asn1s) 

1235 )) 

1236 

1237 def _format_class_tag(self, class_, tag): 

1238 """ 

1239 :return: 

1240 A unicode string of a human-friendly representation of the class and tag 

1241 """ 

1242 

1243 return '[%s %s]' % (CLASS_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP[class_].upper(), tag) 

1244 

1245 def _copy(self, other, copy_func): 

1246 """ 

1247 Copies the contents of another Choice object to itself 

1248 

1249 :param object: 

1250 Another instance of the same class 

1251 

1252 :param copy_func: 

1253 An reference of copy.copy() or copy.deepcopy() to use when copying 

1254 lists, dicts and objects 

1255 """ 

1256 

1257 super(Choice, self)._copy(other, copy_func) 

1258 self._choice = other._choice 

1259 self._name = other._name 

1260 self._parsed = copy_func(other._parsed)

1262 def dump(self, force=False): 

1263 """ 

1264 Encodes the value using DER 

1265 

1266 :param force: 

1267 If the encoded contents already exist, clear them and regenerate 

1268 to ensure they are in DER format instead of BER format 

1269 

1270 :return: 

1271 A byte string of the DER-encoded value 

1272 """ 

1273 

1274 self.contents = self.chosen.dump(force=force) 

1275 if self._header is None or force: 

1276 self._header = b'' 

1277 if self.explicit is not None: 

1278 for class_, tag in self.explicit: 

1279 self._header = _dump_header(class_, 1, tag, self._header + self.contents) + self._header 

1280 return self._header + self.contents

1283class Concat(object): 

1284 """ 

1285 A class that contains two or more encoded child values concatentated 

1286 together. THIS IS NOT PART OF THE ASN.1 SPECIFICATION! This exists to handle 

1287 the x509.TrustedCertificate() class for OpenSSL certificates containing 

1288 extra information. 

1289 """ 

1290 

1291 # A list of the specs of the concatenated values 

1292 _child_specs = None 

1293 

1294 _children = None 

1295 

1296 @classmethod 

1297 def load(cls, encoded_data, strict=False): 

1298 """ 

1299 Loads a BER/DER-encoded byte string using the current class as the spec 

1300 

1301 :param encoded_data: 

1302 A byte string of BER or DER encoded data 

1303 

1304 :param strict: 

1305 A boolean indicating if trailing data should be forbidden - if so, a 

1306 ValueError will be raised when trailing data exists 

1307 

1308 :return: 

1309 A Concat object 

1310 """ 

1311 

1312 return cls(contents=encoded_data, strict=strict) 

1313 

1314 def __init__(self, value=None, contents=None, strict=False): 

1315 """ 

1316 :param value: 

1317 A native Python datatype to initialize the object value with 

1318 

1319 :param contents: 

1320 A byte string of the encoded contents of the value 

1321 

1322 :param strict: 

1323 A boolean indicating if trailing data should be forbidden - if so, a 

1324 ValueError will be raised when trailing data exists in contents 

1325 

1326 :raises: 

1327 ValueError - when an error occurs with one of the children 

1328 TypeError - when an error occurs with one of the children 

1329 """ 

1330 

1331 if contents is not None: 

1332 try: 

1333 contents_len = len(contents) 

1334 self._children = [] 

1335 

1336 offset = 0 

1337 for spec in self._child_specs: 

1338 if offset < contents_len: 

1339 child_value, offset = _parse_build(contents, pointer=offset, spec=spec) 

1340 else: 

1341 child_value = spec() 

1342 self._children.append(child_value) 

1343 

1344 if strict and offset != contents_len: 

1345 extra_bytes = contents_len - offset 

1346 raise ValueError('Extra data - %d bytes of trailing data were provided' % extra_bytes) 

1347 

1348 except (ValueError, TypeError) as e: 

1349 args = e.args[1:] 

1350 e.args = (e.args[0] + '\n while constructing %s' % type_name(self),) + args 

1351 raise e 

1352 

1353 if value is not None: 

1354 if self._children is None: 

1355 self._children = [None] * len(self._child_specs) 

1356 for index, data in enumerate(value): 

1357 self.__setitem__(index, data)

1572class Primitive(Asn1Value): 

1573 """ 

1574 Sets the class_ and method attributes for primitive, universal values 

1575 """ 

1576 

1577 class_ = 0 

1578 

1579 method = 0 

1580 

1581 def __init__(self, value=None, default=None, contents=None, **kwargs): 

1582 """ 

1583 Sets the value of the object before passing to Asn1Value.__init__() 

1584 

1585 :param value: 

1586 A native Python datatype to initialize the object value with 

1587 

1588 :param default: 

1589 The default value if no value is specified 

1590 

1591 :param contents: 

1592 A byte string of the encoded contents of the value 

1593 """ 

1594 

1595 Asn1Value.__init__(self, **kwargs) 

1596 

1597 try: 

1598 if contents is not None: 

1599 self.contents = contents 

1600 

1601 elif value is not None: 

1602 self.set(value) 

1603 

1604 elif default is not None: 

1605 self.set(default) 

1606 

1607 except (ValueError, TypeError) as e: 

1608 args = e.args[1:] 

1609 e.args = (e.args[0] + '\n while constructing %s' % type_name(self),) + args 

1610 raise e

1636 """

1654 def __ne__(self, other): 

1655 return not self == other

1657 def __eq__(self, other): 

1658 """ 

1659 :param other: 

1660 The other Primitive to compare to 

1661 

1662 :return: 

1663 A boolean 

1664 """ 

1665 

1666 if not isinstance(other, Primitive): 

1667 return False 

1668 

1669 if self.contents != other.contents: 

1670 return False 

1671 

1672 # We compare class tag numbers since object tag numbers could be 

1673 # different due to implicit or explicit tagging 

1674 if self.__class__.tag != other.__class__.tag: 

1675 return False 

1676 

1677 if self.__class__ == other.__class__ and self.contents == other.contents: 

1678 return True 

1679 

1680 # If the objects share a common base class that is not too low-level 

1681 # then we can compare the contents 

1682 self_bases = (set(self.__class__.__bases__) | set([self.__class__])) - set([Asn1Value, Primitive, ValueMap]) 

1683 other_bases = (set(other.__class__.__bases__) | set([other.__class__])) - set([Asn1Value, Primitive, ValueMap]) 

1684 if self_bases | other_bases: 

1685 return self.contents == other.contents 

1686 

1687 # When tagging is going on, do the extra work of constructing new 

1688 # objects to see if the dumped representation are the same 

1689 if self.implicit or self.explicit or other.implicit or other.explicit: 

1690 return self.untag().dump() == other.untag().dump() 

1691 

1692 return self.dump() == other.dump()

1910class BitString(Constructable, Castable, Primitive, ValueMap, object): 

1911 """ 

1912 Represents a bit string from ASN.1 as a Python tuple of 1s and 0s 

1913 """ 

1914 

1915 tag = 3 

1916 

1917 _size = None 

1918 

1919 # Used with _as_chunk() from Constructable 

1920 _chunk = None 

1921 _chunks_offset = 1 

1922 

1923 def _setup(self): 

1924 """ 

1925 Generates _reverse_map from _map 

1926 """ 

1927 

1928 ValueMap._setup(self) 

1929 

1930 cls = self.__class__ 

1931 if cls._map is not None: 

1932 cls._size = max(self._map.keys()) + 1 

1933 

1934 def set(self, value): 

1935 """ 

1936 Sets the value of the object 

1937 

1938 :param value: 

1939 An integer or a tuple of integers 0 and 1 

1940 

1941 :raises: 

1942 ValueError - when an invalid value is passed 

1943 """ 

1944 

1945 if isinstance(value, set): 

1946 if self._map is None: 

1947 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

1948 ''' 

1949 %s._map has not been defined 

1950 ''', 

1951 type_name(self) 

1952 )) 

1953 

1954 bits = [0] * self._size 

1955 self._native = value 

1956 for index in range(0, self._size): 

1957 key = self._map.get(index) 

1958 if key is None: 

1959 continue 

1960 if key in value: 

1961 bits[index] = 1 

1962 

1963 value = ''.join(map(str_cls, bits)) 

1964 

1965 elif value.__class__ == tuple: 

1966 if self._map is None: 

1967 self._native = value 

1968 else: 

1969 self._native = set() 

1970 for index, bit in enumerate(value): 

1971 if bit: 

1972 name = self._map.get(index, index) 

1973 self._native.add(name) 

1974 value = ''.join(map(str_cls, value)) 

1975 

1976 else: 

1977 raise TypeError(unwrap( 

1978 ''' 

1979 %s value must be a tuple of ones and zeros or a set of unicode 

1980 strings, not %s 

1981 ''', 

1982 type_name(self), 

1983 type_name(value) 

1984 )) 

1985 

1986 self._chunk = None 

1987 

1988 if self._map is not None: 

1989 if len(value) > self._size: 

1990 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

1991 ''' 

1992 %s value must be at most %s bits long, specified was %s long 

1993 ''', 

1994 type_name(self), 

1995 self._size, 

1996 len(value) 

1997 )) 

1998 # A NamedBitList must have trailing zero bit truncated. See 

1999 # https://www.itu.int/ITU-T/studygroups/com17/languages/X.690-0207.pdf 

2000 # section 11.2, 

2001 # https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5280#page-134 and 

2002 # https://www.ietf.org/mail-archive/web/pkix/current/msg10443.html 

2003 value = value.rstrip('0') 

2004 size = len(value) 

2005 

2006 size_mod = size % 8 

2007 extra_bits = 0 

2008 if size_mod != 0: 

2009 extra_bits = 8 - size_mod 

2010 value += '0' * extra_bits 

2011 

2012 size_in_bytes = int(math.ceil(size / 8)) 

2013 

2014 if extra_bits: 

2015 extra_bits_byte = int_to_bytes(extra_bits) 

2016 else: 

2017 extra_bits_byte = b'\x00' 

2018 

2019 if value == '': 

2020 value_bytes = b'' 

2021 else: 

2022 value_bytes = int_to_bytes(int(value, 2)) 

2023 if len(value_bytes) != size_in_bytes: 

2024 value_bytes = (b'\x00' * (size_in_bytes - len(value_bytes))) + value_bytes 

2025 

2026 self.contents = extra_bits_byte + value_bytes 

2027 self._header = None 

2028 if self._indefinite: 

2029 self._indefinite = False 

2030 self.method = 0 

2031 if self._trailer != b'': 

2032 self._trailer = b''

2034 def __getitem__(self, key): 

2035 """ 

2036 Retrieves a boolean version of one of the bits based on a name from the 

2037 _map 

2038 

2039 :param key: 

2040 The unicode string of one of the bit names 

2041 

2042 :raises: 

2043 ValueError - when _map is not set or the key name is invalid 

2044 

2045 :return: 

2046 A boolean if the bit is set 

2047 """ 

2048 

2049 is_int = isinstance(key, int_types) 

2050 if not is_int: 

2051 if not isinstance(self._map, dict): 

2052 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

2053 ''' 

2054 %s._map has not been defined 

2055 ''', 

2056 type_name(self) 

2057 )) 

2058 

2059 if key not in self._reverse_map: 

2060 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

2061 ''' 

2062 %s._map does not contain an entry for "%s" 

2063 ''', 

2064 type_name(self), 

2065 key 

2066 )) 

2067 

2068 if self._native is None: 

2069 self.native 

2070 

2071 if self._map is None: 

2072 if len(self._native) >= key + 1: 

2073 return bool(self._native[key]) 

2074 return False 

2075 

2076 if is_int: 

2077 key = self._map.get(key, key) 

2078 

2079 return key in self._native

2081 def __setitem__(self, key, value): 

2082 """ 

2083 Sets one of the bits based on a name from the _map 

2084 

2085 :param key: 

2086 The unicode string of one of the bit names 

2087 

2088 :param value: 

2089 A boolean value 

2090 

2091 :raises: 

2092 ValueError - when _map is not set or the key name is invalid 

2093 """ 

2094 

2095 is_int = isinstance(key, int_types) 

2096 if not is_int: 

2097 if self._map is None: 

2098 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

2099 ''' 

2100 %s._map has not been defined 

2101 ''', 

2102 type_name(self) 

2103 )) 

2104 

2105 if key not in self._reverse_map: 

2106 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

2107 ''' 

2108 %s._map does not contain an entry for "%s" 

2109 ''', 

2110 type_name(self), 

2111 key 

2112 )) 

2113 

2114 if self._native is None: 

2115 self.native 

2116 

2117 if self._map is None: 

2118 new_native = list(self._native) 

2119 max_key = len(new_native) - 1 

2120 if key > max_key: 

2121 new_native.extend([0] * (key - max_key)) 

2122 new_native[key] = 1 if value else 0 

2123 self._native = tuple(new_native) 

2124 

2125 else: 

2126 if is_int: 

2127 key = self._map.get(key, key) 

2128 

2129 if value: 

2130 if key not in self._native: 

2131 self._native.add(key) 

2132 else: 

2133 if key in self._native: 

2134 self._native.remove(key) 

2135 

2136 self.set(self._native)

2138 def _as_chunk(self): 

2139 """ 

2140 Allows reconstructing indefinite length values 

2141 

2142 :return: 

2143 A tuple of integers 

2144 """ 

2145 

2146 extra_bits = int_from_bytes(self.contents[0:1]) 

2147 bit_string = '{0:b}'.format(int_from_bytes(self.contents[1:])) 

2148 byte_len = len(self.contents[1:]) 

2149 bit_len = len(bit_string) 

2150 

2151 # Left-pad the bit string to a byte multiple to ensure we didn't 

2152 # lose any zero bits on the left 

2153 mod_bit_len = bit_len % 8 

2154 if mod_bit_len != 0: 

2155 bit_string = ('0' * (8 - mod_bit_len)) + bit_string 

2156 bit_len = len(bit_string) 

2157 

2158 if bit_len // 8 < byte_len: 

2159 missing_bytes = byte_len - (bit_len // 8) 

2160 bit_string = ('0' * (8 * missing_bytes)) + bit_string 

2161 

2162 # Trim off the extra bits on the right used to fill the last byte 

2163 if extra_bits > 0: 

2164 bit_string = bit_string[0:0 - extra_bits] 

2165 

2166 return tuple(map(int, tuple(bit_string))) 

2167 

2168 @property 

2169 def native(self): 

2170 """ 

2171 The a native Python datatype representation of this value 

2172 

2173 :return: 

2174 If a _map is set, a set of names, or if no _map is set, a tuple of 

2175 integers 1 and 0. None if no value. 

2176 """ 

2177 

2178 # For BitString we default the value to be all zeros 

2179 if self.contents is None: 

2180 if self._map is None: 

2181 self.set(()) 

2182 else: 

2183 self.set(set()) 

2184 

2185 if self._native is None: 

2186 bits = self._merge_chunks() 

2187 if self._map: 

2188 self._native = set() 

2189 for index, bit in enumerate(bits): 

2190 if bit: 

2191 name = self._map.get(index, index) 

2192 self._native.add(name) 

2193 else: 

2194 self._native = bits 

2195 return self._native

3122 if value is None and default is not None: 

3123 check_existing = True

3453 def _determine_spec(self, index): 

3454 """

3456

3470 value_spec = field_spec 

3471 spec_override = None 

3472

3480 field_spec, value_spec = spec_override 

3481 if value_spec is None: 

3482 value_spec = field_spec 

3483 spec_override = None

3489 else:

3517 The value to construct an Asn1Value object from

3520 An instance of a child class of Asn1Value 

3521 """ 

3522 

3523 if value is None and 'optional' in field_params: 

3524 return VOID 

3525 

3526 specs_different = field_spec != value_spec 

3527 is_any = issubclass(field_spec, Any) 

3528 

3529 if issubclass(value_spec, Choice):

3544 else: 

3545 new_value = value 

3546 

3547 elif isinstance(value, field_spec): 

3548 new_value = value 

3549 if specs_different: 

3550 new_value.parse(value_spec) 

3551 

3552 elif (not specs_different or is_any) and not isinstance(value, value_spec): 

3553 new_value = value_spec(value, **field_params) 

3554 

3555 else: 

3556 if isinstance(value, value_spec): 

3557 new_value = value 

3558 else: 

3559 new_value = value_spec(value) 

3560 

3561 # For when the field is OctetString or OctetBitString with embedded

4176 def _parse_children(self, recurse=False): 

4177 """ 

4178 Parses the contents and generates Asn1Value objects based on the 

4179 definitions from _child_spec.

4190 self.children = [] 

4191 if self._contents is None:

4206 except (ValueError, TypeError) as e:

4298class Set(Sequence): 

4299 """ 

4300 Represents a set of fields (unordered) from ASN.1 as a Python object with a 

4301 dict-like interface 

4302 """ 

4303 

4304 method = 1 

4305 class_ = 0 

4306 tag = 17 

4307 

4308 # A dict of 2-element tuples in the form (class_, tag) as keys and integers 

4309 # as values that are the index of the field in _fields 

4310 _field_ids = None 

4311 

4312 def _setup(self): 

4313 """ 

4314 Generates _field_map, _field_ids and _oid_nums for use in parsing 

4315 """ 

4316 

4317 cls = self.__class__ 

4318 cls._field_map = {} 

4319 cls._field_ids = {} 

4320 cls._precomputed_specs = [] 

4321 for index, field in enumerate(cls._fields): 

4322 if len(field) < 3: 

4323 field = field + ({},) 

4324 cls._fields[index] = field 

4325 cls._field_map[field[0]] = index 

4326 cls._field_ids[_build_id_tuple(field[2], field[1])] = index 

4327 

4328 if cls._oid_pair is not None: 

4329 cls._oid_nums = (cls._field_map[cls._oid_pair[0]], cls._field_map[cls._oid_pair[1]]) 

4330 

4331 for index, field in enumerate(cls._fields): 

4332 has_callback = cls._spec_callbacks is not None and field[0] in cls._spec_callbacks 

4333 is_mapped_oid = cls._oid_nums is not None and cls._oid_nums[1] == index 

4334 if has_callback or is_mapped_oid: 

4335 cls._precomputed_specs.append(None) 

4336 else: 

4337 cls._precomputed_specs.append((field[0], field[1], field[1], field[2], None))

4339 def _parse_children(self, recurse=False): 

4340 """ 

4341 Parses the contents and generates Asn1Value objects based on the 

4342 definitions from _fields. 

4343 

4344 :param recurse: 

4345 If child objects that are Sequence or SequenceOf objects should 

4346 be recursively parsed 

4347 

4348 :raises: 

4349 ValueError - when an error occurs parsing child objects 

4350 """ 

4351 

4352 cls = self.__class__ 

4353 if self._contents is None: 

4354 if self._fields: 

4355 self.children = [VOID] * len(self._fields) 

4356 for index, (_, _, params) in enumerate(self._fields): 

4357 if 'default' in params: 

4358 if cls._precomputed_specs[index]: 

4359 field_name, field_spec, value_spec, field_params, _ = cls._precomputed_specs[index] 

4360 else: 

4361 field_name, field_spec, value_spec, field_params, _ = self._determine_spec(index) 

4362 self.children[index] = self._make_value(field_name, field_spec, value_spec, field_params, None) 

4363 return 

4364 

4365 try: 

4366 child_map = {} 

4367 contents_length = len(self.contents) 

4368 child_pointer = 0 

4369 seen_field = 0 

4370 while child_pointer < contents_length: 

4371 parts, child_pointer = _parse(self.contents, contents_length, pointer=child_pointer) 

4372 

4373 id_ = (parts[0], parts[2]) 

4374 

4375 field = self._field_ids.get(id_) 

4376 if field is None: 

4377 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

4378 ''' 

4379 Data for field %s (%s class, %s method, tag %s) does 

4380 not match any of the field definitions 

4381 ''', 

4382 seen_field, 

4383 CLASS_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP.get(parts[0]), 

4384 METHOD_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP.get(parts[1]), 

4385 parts[2], 

4386 )) 

4387 

4388 _, field_spec, value_spec, field_params, spec_override = ( 

4389 cls._precomputed_specs[field] or self._determine_spec(field)) 

4390 

4391 if field_spec is None or (spec_override and issubclass(field_spec, Any)): 

4392 field_spec = value_spec 

4393 spec_override = None 

4394 

4395 if spec_override: 

4396 child = parts + (field_spec, field_params, value_spec) 

4397 else: 

4398 child = parts + (field_spec, field_params) 

4399 

4400 if recurse: 

4401 child = _build(*child) 

4402 if isinstance(child, (Sequence, SequenceOf)): 

4403 child._parse_children(recurse=True) 

4404 

4405 child_map[field] = child 

4406 seen_field += 1 

4407 

4408 total_fields = len(self._fields) 

4409 

4410 for index in range(0, total_fields): 

4411 if index in child_map: 

4412 continue 

4413 

4414 name, field_spec, value_spec, field_params, spec_override = ( 

4415 cls._precomputed_specs[index] or self._determine_spec(index)) 

4416 

4417 if field_spec is None or (spec_override and issubclass(field_spec, Any)): 

4418 field_spec = value_spec 

4419 spec_override = None 

4420 

4421 missing = False 

4422 

4423 if not field_params: 

4424 missing = True 

4425 elif 'optional' not in field_params and 'default' not in field_params: 

4426 missing = True 

4427 elif 'optional' in field_params: 

4428 child_map[index] = VOID 

4429 elif 'default' in field_params: 

4430 child_map[index] = field_spec(**field_params) 

4431 

4432 if missing: 

4433 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

4434 ''' 

4435 Missing required field "%s" from %s 

4436 ''', 

4437 name, 

4438 type_name(self) 

4439 )) 

4440 

4441 self.children = [] 

4442 for index in range(0, total_fields): 

4443 self.children.append(child_map[index]) 

4444 

4445 except (ValueError, TypeError) as e: 

4446 args = e.args[1:] 

4447 e.args = (e.args[0] + '\n while parsing %s' % type_name(self),) + args 

4448 raise e

4450 def _set_contents(self, force=False): 

4451 """ 

4452 Encodes all child objects into the contents for this object. 

4453 

4454 This method is overridden because a Set needs to be encoded by 

4455 removing defaulted fields and then sorting the fields by tag. 

4456 

4457 :param force: 

4458 Ensure all contents are in DER format instead of possibly using 

4459 cached BER-encoded data 

4460 """ 

4461 

4462 if self.children is None: 

4463 self._parse_children() 

4464 

4465 child_tag_encodings = [] 

4466 for index, child in enumerate(self.children): 

4467 child_encoding = child.dump(force=force) 

4468 

4469 # Skip encoding defaulted children 

4470 name, spec, field_params = self._fields[index] 

4471 if 'default' in field_params: 

4472 if spec(**field_params).dump() == child_encoding: 

4473 continue 

4474 

4475 child_tag_encodings.append((child.tag, child_encoding)) 

4476 child_tag_encodings.sort(key=lambda ct: ct[0]) 

4477 

4478 self._contents = b''.join([ct[1] for ct in child_tag_encodings]) 

4479 self._header = None 

4480 if self._trailer != b'': 

4481 self._trailer = b''

4569class AbstractTime(AbstractString): 

4570 """ 

4571 Represents a time from ASN.1 as a Python datetime.datetime object 

4572 """ 

4573 

4574 @property 

4575 def native(self): 

4576 """ 

4577 The a native Python datatype representation of this value 

4578 

4579 :return: 

4580 A datetime.datetime object in the UTC timezone or None 

4581 """ 

4582 

4583 if self.contents is None: 

4584 return None 

4585 

4586 if self._native is None: 

4587 string = str_cls(self) 

4588 has_timezone = re.search('[-\\+]', string) 

4589 

4590 # We don't know what timezone it is in, or it is UTC because of a Z 

4591 # suffix, so we just assume UTC 

4592 if not has_timezone: 

4593 string = string.rstrip('Z') 

4594 date = self._date_by_len(string) 

4595 self._native = date.replace(tzinfo=timezone.utc) 

4596 

4597 else: 

4598 # Python 2 doesn't support the %z format code, so we have to manually 

4599 # process the timezone offset. 

4600 date = self._date_by_len(string[0:-5]) 

4601 

4602 hours = int(string[-4:-2]) 

4603 minutes = int(string[-2:]) 

4604 delta = timedelta(hours=abs(hours), minutes=minutes) 

4605 if hours < 0: 

4606 date -= delta 

4607 else: 

4608 date += delta 

4609 

4610 self._native = date.replace(tzinfo=timezone.utc) 

4611 

4612 return self._native

4845def _tag_type_to_explicit_implicit(params): 

4846 """ 

4847 Converts old-style "tag_type" and "tag" params to "explicit" and "implicit" 

4848 

4849 :param params: 

4850 A dict of parameters to convert from tag_type/tag to explicit/implicit 

4851 """ 

4852 

4853 if 'tag_type' in params: 

4854 if params['tag_type'] == 'explicit': 

4855 params['explicit'] = (params.get('class', 2), params['tag']) 

4856 elif params['tag_type'] == 'implicit':

4866 Checks if a value is properly tagged based on the spec, and re/untags as 

4867 necessary

4869 :param value: 

4870 An Asn1Value object 

4871 

4872 :param params:

4874 

4875 :return: 

4876 An Asn1Value that is properly tagged 

4877 """ 

4878 

4879 _tag_type_to_explicit_implicit(params) 

4880 

4881 retag = False 

4882 if 'implicit' not in params: 

4883 if value.implicit is not False: 

4884 retag = True 

4885 else:

4887 class_, tag = params['implicit'] 

4888 else:

4981def _build(class_, method, tag, header, contents, trailer, spec=None, spec_params=None, nested_spec=None): 

4982 """ 

4983 Builds an Asn1Value object generically, or using a spec with optional params 

4984 

4985 :param class_: 

4986 An integer representing the ASN.1 class 

4987 

4988 :param method: 

4989 An integer representing the ASN.1 method 

4990 

4991 :param tag: 

4992 An integer representing the ASN.1 tag 

4993 

4994 :param header: 

4995 A byte string of the ASN.1 header (class, method, tag, length) 

4996 

4997 :param contents: 

4998 A byte string of the ASN.1 value 

4999 

5000 :param trailer: 

5001 A byte string of any ASN.1 trailer (only used by indefinite length encodings) 

5002 

5003 :param spec: 

5004 A class derived from Asn1Value that defines what class_ and tag the 

5005 value should have, and the semantics of the encoded value. The 

5006 return value will be of this type. If omitted, the encoded value 

5007 will be decoded using the standard universal tag based on the 

5008 encoded tag number. 

5009 

5010 :param spec_params: 

5011 A dict of params to pass to the spec object 

5012 

5013 :param nested_spec: 

5014 For certain Asn1Value classes (such as OctetString and BitString), the 

5015 contents can be further parsed and interpreted as another Asn1Value. 

5016 This parameter controls the spec for that sub-parsing. 

5017 

5018 :return: 

5019 An object of the type spec, or if not specified, a child of Asn1Value 

5020 """ 

5021 

5022 if spec_params is not None: 

5023 _tag_type_to_explicit_implicit(spec_params) 

5024 

5025 if header is None: 

5026 return VOID 

5027 

5028 header_set = False 

5029 

5030 # If an explicit specification was passed in, make sure it matches 

5031 if spec is not None: 

5032 # If there is explicit tagging and contents, we have to split 

5033 # the header and trailer off before we do the parsing 

5034 no_explicit = spec_params and 'no_explicit' in spec_params 

5035 if not no_explicit and (spec.explicit or (spec_params and 'explicit' in spec_params)): 

5036 if spec_params: 

5037 value = spec(**spec_params) 

5038 else: 

5039 value = spec() 

5040 original_explicit = value.explicit 

5041 explicit_info = reversed(original_explicit) 

5042 parsed_class = class_ 

5043 parsed_method = method 

5044 parsed_tag = tag 

5045 to_parse = contents 

5046 explicit_header = header 

5047 explicit_trailer = trailer or b'' 

5048 for expected_class, expected_tag in explicit_info: 

5049 if parsed_class != expected_class: 

5050 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

5051 ''' 

5052 Error parsing %s - explicitly-tagged class should have been 

5053 %s, but %s was found 

5054 ''', 

5055 type_name(value), 

5056 CLASS_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP.get(expected_class), 

5057 CLASS_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP.get(parsed_class, parsed_class) 

5058 )) 

5059 if parsed_method != 1: 

5060 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

5061 ''' 

5062 Error parsing %s - explicitly-tagged method should have 

5063 been %s, but %s was found 

5064 ''', 

5065 type_name(value), 

5066 METHOD_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP.get(1), 

5067 METHOD_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP.get(parsed_method, parsed_method) 

5068 )) 

5069 if parsed_tag != expected_tag: 

5070 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

5071 ''' 

5072 Error parsing %s - explicitly-tagged tag should have been 

5073 %s, but %s was found 

5074 ''', 

5075 type_name(value), 

5076 expected_tag, 

5077 parsed_tag 

5078 )) 

5079 info, _ = _parse(to_parse, len(to_parse)) 

5080 parsed_class, parsed_method, parsed_tag, parsed_header, to_parse, parsed_trailer = info 

5081 explicit_header += parsed_header 

5082 explicit_trailer = parsed_trailer + explicit_trailer 

5083 

5084 value = _build(*info, spec=spec, spec_params={'no_explicit': True}) 

5085 value._header = explicit_header 

5086 value._trailer = explicit_trailer 

5087 value.explicit = original_explicit 

5088 header_set = True 

5089 else: 

5090 if spec_params: 

5091 value = spec(contents=contents, **spec_params) 

5092 else: 

5093 value = spec(contents=contents) 

5094 

5095 if spec is Any: 

5096 pass 

5097 

5098 elif isinstance(value, Choice): 

5099 value.validate(class_, tag, contents) 

5100 try: 

5101 # Force parsing the Choice now 

5102 value.contents = header + value.contents 

5103 header = b'' 

5104 value.parse() 

5105 except (ValueError, TypeError) as e: 

5106 args = e.args[1:] 

5107 e.args = (e.args[0] + '\n while parsing %s' % type_name(value),) + args 

5108 raise e 

5109 

5110 else: 

5111 if class_ != value.class_: 

5112 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

5113 ''' 

5114 Error parsing %s - class should have been %s, but %s was 

5115 found 

5116 ''', 

5117 type_name(value), 

5118 CLASS_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP.get(value.class_), 

5119 CLASS_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP.get(class_, class_) 

5120 )) 

5121 if method != value.method: 

5122 # Allow parsing a primitive method as constructed if the value 

5123 # is indefinite length. This is to allow parsing BER. 

5124 ber_indef = method == 1 and value.method == 0 and trailer == b'\x00\x00' 

5125 if not ber_indef or not isinstance(value, Constructable): 

5126 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

5127 ''' 

5128 Error parsing %s - method should have been %s, but %s was found 

5129 ''', 

5130 type_name(value), 

5131 METHOD_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP.get(value.method), 

5132 METHOD_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP.get(method, method) 

5133 )) 

5134 else: 

5135 value.method = method 

5136 value._indefinite = True 

5137 if tag != value.tag and tag != value._bad_tag: 

5138 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

5139 ''' 

5140 Error parsing %s - tag should have been %s, but %s was found 

5141 ''', 

5142 type_name(value), 

5143 value.tag, 

5144 tag 

5145 )) 

5146 

5147 # For explicitly tagged, un-speced parsings, we use a generic container 

5148 # since we will be parsing the contents and discarding the outer object 

5149 # anyway a little further on 

5150 elif spec_params and 'explicit' in spec_params: 

5151 original_value = Asn1Value(contents=contents, **spec_params) 

5152 original_explicit = original_value.explicit 

5153 

5154 to_parse = contents 

5155 explicit_header = header 

5156 explicit_trailer = trailer or b'' 

5157 for expected_class, expected_tag in reversed(original_explicit): 

5158 info, _ = _parse(to_parse, len(to_parse)) 

5159 _, _, _, parsed_header, to_parse, parsed_trailer = info 

5160 explicit_header += parsed_header 

5161 explicit_trailer = parsed_trailer + explicit_trailer 

5162 value = _build(*info, spec=spec, spec_params={'no_explicit': True}) 

5163 value._header = header + value._header 

5164 value._trailer += trailer or b'' 

5165 value.explicit = original_explicit 

5166 header_set = True 

5167 

5168 # If no spec was specified, allow anything and just process what 

5169 # is in the input data 

5170 else: 

5171 if tag not in _UNIVERSAL_SPECS: 

5172 raise ValueError(unwrap( 

5173 ''' 

5174 Unknown element - %s class, %s method, tag %s 

5175 ''', 

5176 CLASS_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP.get(class_), 

5177 METHOD_NUM_TO_NAME_MAP.get(method), 

5178 tag 

5179 )) 

5180 

5181 spec = _UNIVERSAL_SPECS[tag] 

5182 

5183 value = spec(contents=contents, class_=class_) 

5184 ber_indef = method == 1 and value.method == 0 and trailer == b'\x00\x00' 

5185 if ber_indef and isinstance(value, Constructable): 

5186 value._indefinite = True 

5187 value.method = method 

5188 

5189 if not header_set: 

5190 value._header = header 

5191 value._trailer = trailer or b'' 

5192 

5193 # Destroy any default value that our contents have overwritten 

5194 value._native = None 

5195 

5196 if nested_spec: 

5197 try: 

5198 value.parse(nested_spec) 

5199 except (ValueError, TypeError) as e: 

5200 args = e.args[1:] 

5201 e.args = (e.args[0] + '\n while parsing %s' % type_name(value),) + args 

5202 raise e 

5203 

5204 return value

5207def _parse_build(encoded_data, pointer=0, spec=None, spec_params=None, strict=False): 

5208 """ 

5209 Parses a byte string generically, or using a spec with optional params 

5210 

5211 :param encoded_data: 

5212 A byte string that contains BER-encoded data 

5213 

5214 :param pointer: 

5215 The index in the byte string to parse from 

5216 

5217 :param spec: 

5218 A class derived from Asn1Value that defines what class_ and tag the 

5219 value should have, and the semantics of the encoded value. The 

5220 return value will be of this type. If omitted, the encoded value 

5221 will be decoded using the standard universal tag based on the 

5222 encoded tag number. 

5223 

5224 :param spec_params: 

5225 A dict of params to pass to the spec object 

5226 

5227 :param strict: 

5228 A boolean indicating if trailing data should be forbidden - if so, a 

5229 ValueError will be raised when trailing data exists 

5230 

5231 :return: 

5232 A 2-element tuple: 

5233 - 0: An object of the type spec, or if not specified, a child of Asn1Value 

5234 - 1: An integer indicating how many bytes were consumed 

5235 """ 

5236 

5237 encoded_len = len(encoded_data) 

5238 info, new_pointer = _parse(encoded_data, encoded_len, pointer) 

5239 if strict and new_pointer != pointer + encoded_len: 

5240 extra_bytes = pointer + encoded_len - new_pointer 

5241 raise ValueError('Extra data - %d bytes of trailing data were provided' % extra_bytes) 

5242 return (_build(*info, spec=spec, spec_params=spec_params), new_pointer)
